    "comment": "Rationale: Combination of knock down and pharmacological inhibitions along with function measures of presynaptic calcium influx shows that CDK5 normally constrains the activity of voltage-gated Ca channels.\n\n23/01/2017 Pim\n- Fig.1 KD of CNa has negative effect on SV exocytosis\n- Fig.2 KD/agonist of CDK5 has positive effect on SV exocytosis\n- Fig.2 Effect of CDK5 and CNa is via VGCCs (shown via VGCC inhibition)\n- Fig.3/4/5/6 CNa and CDK5 activities affect presynaptic Ca influx. Experimental description: Hippocampal CA3-CA1 regions were dissected from 1- to 2-d-old Sprague Dawley rats, dissociated, and plated onto poly-ornithine-coated glass for 14-21 d as described previously (Ryan, 1999).",
